  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study tests the use of a portable mechanical compression device (FM220, Flowmedic, USA)
      for the treatment of claudication and peripheral arterial disease.

      Major endpoints are improved exercise tolerance and relevant blood pressure ratios
    </textblock>
